and Truespace 2 I believe. The magazine was Computer Arts and I think they
may still have the issue with the program as a back order.

Almost unknown to me I already had one 3d program, Corel 3d Dream that came
with my Corel 6 package. After "cutting my teeth on Truespace, I went back
and hit the Corel books and that program, Since Truespace didn\'t have a
manual I missed a lot of truely GOOD things while tinkering with it, I found
out about many of them thriugh the Corel Dream manual.

By luck I found  someone that was looking to get rid of the RayDream 5.2
package, the big brother version to Corel Dream. This was an easier
transition, but now Metacreations is brining out a totally new 3d program,
incorperatin parts of Raydream, parts of Infinity D (?) and an interface
similar to the new poser and Bryce interface. So now I have to decide
whither I want to "upgrade" to another program, and is Carrara (MC\'s
program) the right one.

Lightwave, as Jesse uses it, seems to have some real advantages, but at a
very high cost. Of course the program doesn\'t do it all... even with it I
doubt that I\'d be in Jesse\'s league (well I can wish, but..), so is it worth
the money? Probably not at this time...

Well, that\'s how I started playing with this stuff, and it now consumes MOST
of my free time! My wife uses the names of several 3d artists on this list
as if they contained ony 4 letters... and says that they are going to be
named in the divorce papers, but dang if it isn\'t fun!!!

Mike

