    'body' => 'ROFLMAO!!!!!  No, as far as I know Grandfather had nothing to do with it :)
There is indeed hope for you ;)

Actually, I\'ve mentioned before that nearly ANYONE can LEARN how to do 3D.
In it\'s simplest form all it is is putting together basic primatives to get
your scene.  Take a Merc Cruiser for example.  In it\'s simplest form, it\'s a
big sphere (main hull), four small spheres (main hull turrets), four medium
sized boxes (the "legs"), and four small boxes (the leg turrets).  That\'s
it.  All the rest of the details (what 3D folks generally call "nurnies" and
physical model shops call "greeblies") are just variations on that theme.
Other ship types are more involved, but EVERY single ship that I\'ve ever
done started out as a box, sphere, or cone.  The rest is just subtlety and
texture mapping.

