750,000 people. And I\'m not sure one can claim less diversity anymore up
here.

> They also don\'t get hellish summers,

The summer weather in Canada\'s largest city, Toronto, is about the
same as that of Detroit and Buffalo, and not too different from
Chicago, maybe a tad cooler than Washington DC (but not a lot). Yet
its violent crime rate is a fraction of any of these.

>which has a stastisical effect on violent crime.  We also have a cultural
