> 
> > I don\'t even know if it would be
> > legal to develop something non-commercial based on the MiGE universe
> > for more than personal use.
> 
> There is nothing _illegal_ in people so doing .

Back in the 80s, Chaosium published the Ringworld RPG, covering Niven\'s
Known Space setting.  Niven was involved in this project, so he knows what
RPGs are.  Unfortunately the game itself didn\'t really take off.  I gather
the licence fees tended to hurt Chaosium\'s profit margins too.

SJG used to have an article on their web pages about using GURPS in the
CoDominium setting.  It doesn\'t seem to be there any more.  It was pretty
short, anyway.

There are plenty of unauthorised GURPS versions of various writers\'
universes floating around the Net.  

