At the risk of starting a system war, I\'d say GURPS would handle the whole
setting almost effortlessly.  Like Leading Edge, it\'s a reasonably
realistic system as befits the decidedly realistic feel of Pournelle\'s
books.  And GURPS already has the rules in place to handle the appropriate
technology.  I just picked up Space 3rd Edition, and I think that one could
model the space travel tech used in the CoDominium/MiGE universe with
almost no effort (Jump Drive for Alderson Drive, and a moderately powerful
total conversion drive for the real-space drive.  Further, the default
force screens in GURPS are obviously modeled on the Langston Field (Slow
objects can pass through, beams and fast objects are deflected.  Screens
accumulate energy levels when hit, glowing in different colors as the
levels increase.  Powerful attacks can "blow through" the screen without
destroying it. Etc.)  

