    'ts-index' => '1999-10-31.ec651',
    'body' => 'I ripped off an idea today and I\'m looking for feedback:
\'The General War\' ( a 5FFW variant)
Setup:  Known Space 1107
The 3I is the most powerful military, economic and political presence in
known
space. It has recently (in historical terms) defeated the Zhodani in
4FFW, kept
Vargr raiders plus the Aslan Ihatiei at bay, decimated (for practical
purposes) any dramatically serious insurgent movements in Solomani Rim,
and generally has done everything right for itself since 1082.
These objective realities have sunk in to the rest of the major powers
in known
space.... many are jealous of the successes that the 3I has achieved.
Failures in the domestic or interstellar situation of these major powers
cause  groups within them
to lack dignity and self-respect. They look at the 3I and its successes
and they
become embittered, resentful, even enraged. As they see it, the 3I is
being arrogant, rubbing their nose in it, seeking to dominate all of
known space and beyond.

They decide to act. Sometime around 1107, every major power (Zhodani,
Vargr(s), Aslan, Solomani, Hivers, and the K\'kree) prepares to launch a
simultaneous attack
on the 3I with the objective of destroying it forever.

Ref note:  This idea comes from about 50 billion different sources; the
couple I\'m
prepared to cite are Star Fleet Battles and G:T. SFB has a campaign
dubbed \'the
general war\'; G:T doesn\'t mention anything specific (that I\'ve read
anyway, I only
have the basic G:T rules/sourcebook right now) but they do allude to
border conflicts
and tensions. I figure if 3I gets to many off those going without
resolving them quickly
it could get itself in a sticky situation.

And now, on to our questions:
1. Plausibility:
    a. Could they have the means to launch such a war?
        I would say yes; you wouldn\'t need to have specific minute by
minute timetables;
        all you would need is to send some couriers out to each power
notifying them of
        when they need to strike generally (i.e.. have K\'kree battle
fleets hit these 4 sectors
        during this half of the year).
     b. Would they launch such an attack?
        If the conditions were as stated in the first 3 paragraphs, I
would say yes. But hey,
        that\'s what I think. I\'d like to know what you folks think.
2. Rebellion: would it happen or not?
    Depends; if Dulinor goes off and gets himself killed "for the Glory
of the Empire", then
    I suppose not. On the other hand, if the 3I gets messed up badly and
sues for peace,
    you could have a setup like France and Russia went through after
they lost to the
    Germans (in 1871 / 1917 respectively). Did someone say Paris
Commune?
3. Who would win?
    Ahhhh. Now you now why I sent this in. If the whole of known space
went on the
    warpath, who would win? [Crowd, screaming] 2 fleets enter! 1 fleet
leaves!
4. Finally, has anybody else thought about or done something like this
particular
scenario in Traveler?
Give me the Veedback! Feedflack! Oh, whatever.
