    'body' => '> From: "Kiri Aradia Morgan" <tiamat@tsoft.com>

> ObTrav:  I wonder about different protesting styles in the cultures of the
> Third Imperium.  How do the Vilani protest ANYTHING?  Do the Vargr and the
> Aslan even have demonstrations?  Do the K\'Kree throw paint on old ladies in
> furs?

The Vilani probably have a traditional, sanctioned form of protest that
involves completing official protest forms at the appropriate
administrative office.  Come to think of it, that\'s probably how the
Zhodani handle it, too, except that forms are just a formality to create
a record, because the Tavrchedl have already figured out what the
protestors are upset about and made recommendations to the local noble
council.

How can an outsider even tell if the Vargr are protesting?  In any case,
protest styles will vary extremely across the incredible diversity of
Vargr societies.

The Aslan probably have great traditions of noble and honorable protest,
including carrying petitions to Edo (but not ritual suicide, as I
recall).

The K\'Kree shoot old ladies in furs.

- --Glenn
