    'ts-index' => '1999-11-01.ec772',
    'body' => 'I think alot of people out there got the wrong idea from this post.  The
point of "A Day of Peace" is to have a day where violence is not performed
in any way.  The idea is not that TV shows cause violence, but that by
watching and enjoying images of violence we are somehow celebrating it,
and it would be good if we did not do this for just one day.  Too many of
you had a kind of knee-jerk reaction where you reflexively hugged a
variety of constitutional amendments to your chests.  This has nothing to
do with that.  The "Day of Peace" movement is not anti-gun nor anti-free
speech.  It is anti-violence. 

Charles C.
