Actually, from statements in "Rammer", corpsicles are *not* revivable
with the tech available to "The State". They merely extracted his
memory RNA from the "mush" left by the freeze/thaw damage and dumped it
into a brainwiped criminal. He\'s *not* in his original body.

But I seriously doubt that "The State" existed when the ships in
"Legacy of Heorot", "Beowulf\'s Children" and "Destiny\'s Road" were
launched. It may have sprung up *later* (which might explain the
communications breakdown), but given the way "The State" planned, I
don\'t see them abandoning those colonies. I think this is yet another
Niven universe. It\'s not like he didn\'t *already* have several!

