The article refers to Title 14, section 1211, of the
Code of Federal Regulations (which would be cited as
14 C.F.R. sec. 1211).  I looked for 14 C.F.R. sec.
1211 on the web, and found that it is a reserved
section -- that is, there is no section there now, but
they want to leave that number free to put in a
regulation in the future.  I was not able to look as
far back as 1969, the purported date when that
regulation was promulgated.

14 C.F.R. secs. 1200-1299 regulate NASA.  Section 1211
comes between section 1210, "Development work for
industry in NASA wind tunnels," and section 1212,
"Privacy Act-NASA regulations."  

The table of contents for title 14 follows at the end
of this message, edited by me for format (that is,
page numbers and dots deleted).

If I can be of further assistance, please email me
directly at gmgoffin@yahoo.com.

- --Glenn M. Goffin, Esq.

