    'month' => '11',
    'index' => 'ec872',
    'body' => 'William Prankard <cmdrx@magicnet.net> wrote:

> David Summers wrote:
>
> > Can anyone tell me what hex Scangen is in?  (In the Gvurdon Sector)  I have
> > the GDW Alien module and I\'m running the Traveller Adventure and I was
> > going to point it out to my players, but if it says exactly where it is,
> > I can\'t find it.
>
> According to my Gal2.4 Gvurrdon data, "Classic Era"(c. 1100):
>
> Scangen       2937 B88557A-C    Ni As              224 Vk
> 
> Subsector P-Firgr  and Vk is Commonality of Kedzudh

I think that was an arbitrary, non-canon placement by Roger Myhre for his
Gvurrdon work for HIWG.  I\'ve never been convinced by it.

The Traveller Adventure says (p. 77): "...Scangen, a planet in the Vargr
Extents just across the frontier."  For the Bannerji/Sternmetal scam to
be worthwhile, then they\'ll want to pick a Vargr world as close to the 
border as possible as the supposed source of the Lewis lanthanum they\'re
passing as Vargr ore.  Bannerji has to be kept idle on Aramanx until his 
ship has burned the time it takes to reach Scangen and return to Junidy;
the longer he has to hide, the longer he has to stay idle, and the less
money they can make on the scam.

If he were going to Scangen, Bannerji would leave the Imperium by way of
Jesedipere (the itinerary in his wallet in the Leedor episode says so, 
and shows every other world on his route).  His ship, _Wolblutn_, is a
jump-2 far trader.  If he has to appear to reach 2937, he either has to
waste cargo space on fuel tankage and make a deep space connection, or
take something like an eight jump detour to get there.  I think 2937 is 
too deep in the Extents; it wastes too much time.

There\'s two candidate worlds within jump-2 of Jesedipere that could be
Scangen; 2840 and 2940.  Both have under 1000 inhabitants; 2840 is a 
lawless company rockball with a class-D starport at tech-6, and 2940 is
a balkanized garden world with a class-B starport at tech-8.

I vaguely remember that _Merchant Prince_ might have a reference to a
company based out of Scangen.  Otherwise, take your pick.  2840 would
make a mining hellhole.  2940 could be a trading center built around a
lanthanum rush, with competing Vargr mining operations controlling bits
of the world, while the environmentalists scream at them to protect the
local ecosystem....  There might also be other references to Scangen in
backstory related to Oberlindes Lines and the _Emissary_ -- I think the
_Emissary_ might be based out of Scangen.  If so, I\'d lean toward the
better starport (2940).

  -- Steve Bonneville
