    'date' => 'Tue, 2 Nov 1999 10:20:38  0500 (EST)',
    'body' => 'Hi All. (warning, mild spoilers ahead, if you don\'t want to know anything
about "Destiny\'s Road", don\'t read the rest). 



Regarding "Destiny\'s Road" and "The State", I\'m quite certain they\'re in
the same universe.  The thing that makes me think so is that they mention
"proles" and "citizens" (in passing, but still) in DR.  Also, they have
the whole discussion about "Hydraulic Empires" in it, which was also in
AWooT.  I don\'t recall similar concepts in "Legacy of Herot" (sp?) so I
suspect that\'s a different universe.

Note that DR was started several years ago by Niven and only completed
recently (He\'s said something about "The State" being depressing, so maybe
that blocked him :-) . I\'m not sure about the dates, but that may put its
original conception in the pre-LoH era.  Also, DR is written by Niven
alone, not in collaboration with Pournelle or Barnes. 

