    'index' => 'ec879',
    'month' => '11',
    'body' => '	I think the idea of every major power joining in an attack on the
Imperium is a cool idea.  I\'m not sure I see them as joining forces in any
overt way, but certainly people might "jump on the bandwagon" once the 3I
showed weakness.  Personally I think this would quickly result in the
decimation of the 3I as they would be fighting wars on too many fronts. 
	I could see the K\'Kree starting the whole thing simply because
they decide they want to "wipe out the f***ing meat eaters".  Vargr bands
might take this as a good time to do some land grabs.  With forces being
drained away to deal with these problems, the Zhos might see an
opportunity to push the "expansionistic pluralists" back to Corridor and
the Sols might see a chance to regain Terra.  Aslan Ihatei are already
pestering the rimward Marches, they might start making incursions
elsewhere if Imp forces got weak enough.  The Hivers would definately not
join in, IMO.  They might in fact help the 3I in their own particularly
subtle ways... :-)

	This all stretches socio-economic realism, mind you.  But my
general advice is: Don\'t let excessive realism stand in the way of
excessive coolness.  Epic grandeur generally requires stretching reality a
bit. 

	I\'ve always thought a Sixth Frontier War would be cool, with the
Ihatei joining Zho, Vargr and Sword Worlds forces.  That would be a pretty
tough bind for the Marches, IMO.

Have a good one,
Charles C.
