    'index' => 'ec902',
    'month' => '11',
    'body' => 'Greetings:

As best as I can tell, there are actually ***three*** Niven series that deal 
with STL travel...

The "Leshy Circuit" (names take from James Branch Cabell\'s fantasy stories) 
included a group of short stories published in the early 70\'s. For a list, 
see "Tales of Known Space".

The "State" stories included "Rammer" (latter "World Out of Time"), and then 
the novels "World Out of Time", and the two "Smoke Ring" novels. (From what 
I\'ve read, Niven was working on a third at one point...don\'t know what 
happened...)

The "Beowulf" stories are "Beowulf\'s Children", "Legacy of Heroet" and 
"Destiny\'s Road". These are different from the "State" stories. These have 
the colony ships being launched by the UN, have hibernation which **almost** 
works (the "State" stories, hibernation could only be overcome by injecting 
your memory RNA into a "wiped" person...not good for the person who was 
getting wiped, icky for your corpsicle...). "Beowulf" and "Legacy" take place 
on the planet with the "Grendel\'s", "Destiny\'s Road" clearly takes place in 
the same universe--see the "prologue" of a statement by the head of the 
UN...but a different planet (one is on a planet of Tau Ceti...can\'t remember 
the other star for the other book...).

All this stuff is good, BTW, but three different universes...

Fred Kiesche
(e-mail: Diespamer@aol.com)
(owner of way too many SF books...)
