    'month' => '11',
    'body' => 'Kenneth Bearden wrote:

> > > Scangen       2937 B88557A-C    Ni As              224 Vk
> > >
> > > Subsector P-Firgr  and Vk is Commonality of Kedzudh
> >
> > I think that was an arbitrary, non-canon placement by Roger Myhre for his
> > Gvurrdon work for HIWG.  I\'ve never been convinced by it.
>
> The official Scangen placement is detailed in DGP\'s Vargr&Vilani alien 
> book.  The above placement does sound correct, according to the DGP
> placement (who made beautiful Traveller maps, covering the entire
> Imperium, with exact star placement).

I actually can\'t find any reference to Scangen there.  I did find that 
_Emissary_ is based out of Pandrin (Gvurrdon 2240).  The map for 5FW 
agrees with this; it also shows the worlds Balent (Gvurrdon 2340), 
Uthith (Gvurrdon 2339) and Gireel (Gvurrdon 2338).  V&V claims that
Uthith is at Gvurrdon 2703, but that\'s almost certainly a typo since
that\'s the same as its hex number on the 5FW board.  The 5FW hex number
has nothing to do with any sane sector hex numbering system -- 5FW 2703  
is the same as Gvurrdon 2339 on the board.

I still don\'t like 2937 as the answer, but there isn\'t much counter
evidence either.  Sigh.

  -- Steve Bonneville
