  {
    'body' => '>I get loads of GPFs from Windows Explorer ... even when  its  not
>running!  I now use the Litestep shell but  still  get GPFs  from
>EXPLORER.EXE.  Its almost time  for  the  biannual  reformat  and
>reinstall.

You shouldn\'t be getting any at all.  The prime culprit for those is the
video driver.  Some of them don\'t work in Windows 95 without a tweak or two.
For instance, one card from Matrox I used sets itself at "optimal" which was
causing me Blue screens right and left.  When I experimented and set it for
"adapter default" they went away.

Another thing could be shared DLLs left over from un-installs.  Those will
flake out your system too.  Your plans for a FORMAT will clear this up.  In
fact Microsoft itself advises a yearly formatting and re-installation of
windows.

Another thing could be any odd 16-bit programs that don\'t like windows (or
that windows don\'t like).  Windows is a primarily 32-bit operating system
(noted exceptions gdi.exe and user.exe which are STILL 16-bit).  I have read
that some 16 bit applications will cause system instability.




