Actually, the US does have an \'organized militia\'.  It\'s called the National Guard, and is probably fairly close to what the founders wanted, since they were more states-rights people than democrats per se, and the national guard is under the control of individual states (and does, incidentally, have military equipment).  However, the second amendment is subject to multiple different interpretations; in particular, it is not obvious that the right to bear arms is _limited_ to the creation of a \'well-ordered militia\'.
