    'month' => '11',
    'body' => 'At 09:29 AM 11/3/99 -0500, you wrote:
>Now, it\'s not known if Jaqueline had any other heirs when *she* was gunned
down way back when, since her entire immediate family died with her.  But
her assassin succeeded her.  Cleon the Mad didn\'t have any heirs when he
got whacked.  There were *bound* to be spurious claims to the Throne that
got set aside by the Moot.  Why didn\'t Dulinor stick around and let *them*
decide?  Odds are, they would have found in his favour, since Varian and
Lucan weren\'t in the direct line of succession, merely alternates who would
have gotten further and further from the Throne as Strephon\'s kids produced
more heirs.
>

If Dulinor had stuck around, and was willing to abide by the Moot\'s
decision, they would have decided for Margaret. First, unlike the Emperors
of the Flag, Strephon was very popular. The Moot would not have been
willing to reward his murderer. Two, there were already rumors about how
Varian died going around before Lucan claimed the throne. This would have
cast a pall over the Moot giving him the throne.  Three, Margaret was
already a popular member of the Moot at the time of the assassination.
Giving the throne to someone they knew and trusted would have been the most
logical choice.

Richard Wilson
