And the perils of speaking the "same language" strikes again!

In the US, napkins are the things you wipe your hands and face with
(aka serviettes(sp)). Diapers are what you put on a baby\'s bottom.

And (for our British list members), "knock up" means "make pregnant"
and "fanny" is a synonym for "butt", not for "vagina".

The ObTrav should be obvious. Galanglic will have these sort of
boobytraps for every single world that has a few million or more
"native speakers". 

Which means that if the ref wants some fun, all he has to do is come up
with a different meaning for some common idiom, and watch the confusion.

"Could I have a napkin, please" in a restaraunt, for example. :-)

