    'from' => 'Glenn Goffin gmgoffin@yahoo.com',
    'body' => '>From: "David P. Summers"

>IMO, Imperial right are the right to
>a trial before an impartial judge, the right to 
>present evidence on your behalf, and the right to 
>call witnesses on your behalf.
>Basically it will guarantee the rule of law over 
>arbitrary action by individuals.

No, I don\'t see any _guarantee_ of a _rule of law_ in
the Third Imperium.  I think that the Third Imperium
will try to establish some predictability of result in
order to facilitate interstellar commerce, but beyond
that, due process is just not the controlling concern.
 

Nobles will get more due process than ordinary
citizens; member states will get more due process than
ordinary citizens; megacorporations may or may not get
more due process than ordinary citizens.

Remember that individual member states may grant more
due process to litigants in their jurisdiction than
the Imperium would, so forum selection is a big issue
for lawyers in The Far Future.

- --Glenn

