Yes. The first 250 issues on 5 CDs, plus all 7 issues of The Strategic
Review. These magazines are *in their entirety*, and I mean that. It\'s got
every single comic, game insert, illustration and advertisement in there.

I got it for $44.99 + tax (American), and IMHO it\'s well worth every penny
of it so far.

Compatibility (from the back of the box): "The Dragon Magazine Archive is
partially Macintosh compatible: Our proprietary browser is PC compatible,
but all files are in PDF format, and can be read with Adobe Acrobat Reader."

>OK, now I\'m even more confused, why is it controversial.  Sounds like an
>interesting thing to get to me, wouldn\'t mind a archive of the other
>magazine they had in the early 90\'s (Dungeon, IIRC) either.


TSR had been talking about releasing the archive for some time. However, one
of the big problems concerned reprinting rights for the articles, covers,
comics, etc. The contract that they have people sign doesn\'t (or didn\'t?)
cover reprint rights. There\'s apparently a law that allows publishers to
create "archives" and skip around such contracts. TSR went with that
option... and, well, as a result I\'ve got 250 issues of dragon sitting on
top of my CPU tower.

Some people were mad because the intent of the law in question was to
provide a way for publishers to make archives available in low-print "public
good" runs (for libraries and such places). TSR was very clear that this was
to be a mass-market commercial product. The catch is that in order to be
covered by this law, they had to include every issue they were *in its
entirety.* You get all of the Play By Mail ads, all of the Dragonbone ads,
all of the miniatures ads. In other words, there\'s real interest for general
RPG history geeks as well.

If the Dragon archive succeeds, one for Dungeon magazine can\'t be too far
behind.

> Zane (who is feeling out of touch with the RPG world)


Well, now you\'re back in touch!

If anyone\'s interested Warner / EC has released the Complete Mad Magazine on
CD as well. I\'m salivating as we speak... that\'s one for my Christmas wish
list. ;)
