    'topic' => 'Errata in CT',
    'body' => 'Joseph R. Dietrich writes <tongue in cheek>:

> Errors in the Good Book! Oy vey! What of holy canon! What of rules! Indeed,
> the whole framework of my existence is shaken. Woe is me.

It\'s worse that that. [Is anyone surprised?]  Somehow an apparent typo
crept into later editions of Book 2 on the Drive Potential Table.  Early
print runs show drives Z produce only performance level 5 in 2000-ton
hulls, a consistent interpolation with the rest of the table.  However,
somewhere along the way to later print runs, this got inexplicably bumped
up to an incongruous performance level 6 in 2000-ton hulls, a striking
discontinuity from the level 4 performance drives Y yield, and a notable
anomaly in the mathematical progressions of the overall table.

This presumed typo then persisted on into every printing of the BBL I\'ve
ever seen.

Then, just to thoroughly immortalize it all, The Traveller Adventure
introduces the Imperiallines TI/TJ class, built to Book 2 specs, and
relying on the unusually-high drive performance available to 2000-ton hulls
as a result of the long-overlooked typo to set a particularly significant
bit of canon, namely the "alternative" to the X-Boat system.

Note that the TIs [and hence, de facto, the TJs] are now established as
canonical in CT, G:T, and TNE, and possibly other milieux I haven\'t noticed
them in yet.

Gotta love it... ;)




Chad Russell
This is not a .sig
