    'body' => '> From: "Sword Worlder" 
> I doubt that the general populace had canon or warships or heavy cavalry.

One of the sparks that set off the Paris Commune revolution in 1871 was an
attempt to confiscate the cannon of the Paris National Guard.  

When France surrendered at the end of the Franco-Prussian War, the new
(Republican) government that had replaced Napoleon the Third was supposed
to hand over all their artillery to the Germans.

The National Guard claimed that as their guns had been bought with money
raised by public subscriptions, they were private property, rather than
property of the state, and therefore were not covered by the deal.  They
got away with it!  (At least until the Commune was suppressed.)

So there, at least, was a case where the general populace had cannon.  

