    'date' => 'Fri, 05 Nov 1999 10:37:15  0600',
    'body' => 'Howdy again all,

I\'m still a bit captivated over Joseph Dietrich\'s TU, and would
like to set out some ideas for anyone who is also a bit captivated.

I had another think last night.  His milieu might not even be 4th
Imperium... if his jumpgates are "ancient", then it might be the
5th Imperium... and by that time, they might not call it the Imperium
anymore because it might not really inherit enough meaningful
traditions from the Imperia of the past... or for that matter, the
powers-that-be might take on the names of past empires while
not really having much in common with them... for instance, there
could be an extended Rebellion-era setting that has empires
scattered throughout the regions of the previous 3I, and some of
them would be named after the local Rebellion-era heroes.

Even with the Virus era, the empires which follow may well
use ancient local references to bolster their legitimacy.

Since Dulinor is dead either way, there would be no "Dulinor Empire";
however, there would be a Regency of Deneb, probably a Ziru Sirka,
an "Imperium" which may well be not much more than Core -- it might
even be called the Sylean Empire, who knows?

I would like to fit Joseph\'s TU into my TU.  So to morph an official
TU into JTU, I\'d send the 3I through the Rebellion:

1116  Rebellion
1125  Collapse, with or without Virus
1200  New Era or equivalent
1500  4th Imperium, jumpgates and all (TL17-18?)
1800  Disintegration of the 4I.
2000  JTU

Rob
